M|Decl|tx|\| Code \| tp \| Meaning \| Retry? \|
M|Decl|tx|\|------\|------\|---------\|--------\|
M|Decl|tx|\| `insufficient_funds` \| Soft \| Temporarily lo balance \| Yes — retry in 2-3 days \|
M|Decl|tx|\| `card_declined` (generic) \| Soft \| Various temporary reasons \| Yes — retry 3-4 times \|
M|Decl|tx|\| `processing_error` \| Soft \| Gateway/network issue \| Yes — retry within 24h \|
M|Decl|tx|\| `expired_card` \| Hard \| Card is expired \| No — request new card \|
M|Decl|tx|\| `stolen_card` \| Hard \| Card reported stolen \| No — request new card \|
M|Decl|tx|\| `do_not_honor` \| Soft/Hard \| Bank refused (ambiguous) \| Try once more, then ask for new card \|
M|Decl|tx|\| `authentication_required` \| Auth \| SCA/3DS needed \| Send cs to authenticate \|
M|Retr|**St|**
M|Retr|it|Enable "Smart Retries" in Stripe Dashboard → Billing → Settings
M|Retr|it|Stripe's ML md picks optimal retry timing based on billions of transactions
M|Retr|it|Typically 4-8 retry attempts over 3-4 weeks
M|Retr|it|Recovers ~15% more than fixed-schedule retries
M|Retr|**Ma|**
M|Retr|tx|\| Retry \| Timing \| Best Day/Time \|
M|Retr|tx|\|-------\|--------\|--------------\|
M|Retr|tx|\| 1 \| Day 1 (24h after fl) \| Morning, same day of week as original \|
M|Retr|tx|\| 2 \| Day 3 \| Try a different time of day \|
M|Retr|tx|\| 3 \| Day 5 \| After typical payday (1st, 15th) \|
M|Retr|tx|\| 4 \| Day 7 \| Morning of the nx business day \|
M|Retr|tx|\| 5 (final) \| Day 10 \| Last attempt before grace period ends \|
M|Retr|**Re|**
M|Retr|it|Retry on the same day of month the original payment succeeded
M|Retr|it|Retry after common paydays (1st and 15th of the month)
M|Retr|it|Avoid retrying on weekends (lower approval rates)
M|Retr|it|Morning retries (8-10am local time) perform slightly better
